\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ צמתך\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  as meaning a veil \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ (צמת)\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , where the tav is a radical, for were that so, it would have to be 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ punctuated with a dagesh when immediately preceding a hey, which makes it the feminine 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ possessive, or a vav, which makes it the masculine possessive, like the tav of \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ שבת\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , which, when 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ given to a female, (i.e., in the feminine possessive form), is punctuated with a dagesh, like (Hos. 2: 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ 13): her festival[s], her new moon[s], and her Sabbath[s] \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ (שבתה)\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , and so for the masculine, (Num. 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ 28:10): the burnt offering of a Sabbath in its Sabbath \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ (בשבתו)\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , but the tav of \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ צמתך\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , which is not 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ punctuated with a dagesh, perforce comes instead of a hey, and the name of the kerchief is \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ צמה\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ and when it is possessive, to be given to a male or female, the hey is converted to a tav without 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ a dagesh; e.g. \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ שפחה\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  becomes \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ שפחתו\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  or \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ שפחתה\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , and so \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ אמה\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  [becomes] \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ אמתו\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ אמתה\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  ; \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ ערוה\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  (nakedness) 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ [becomes] \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ ערותו\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ ערותה\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , and likewise, this one, \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ צמה\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  [becomes] \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ צמתו\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ צמתה\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ צמתי\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ צמתך\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ . \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ that 
\lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ streamed\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  Heb. \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ שגלשו\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , that they became bald. \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ גבח\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  is rendered by the Targum as \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ גלוש\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ . When the 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ animals descend from the mountain, the mountain becomes bald and bare of them.  
\par \par }

