\deflang1033\pard\par\plain\par\ql \par\ql \lang1033\ltrch\f6\fs40\b\i0\ul0\cf6\cb14\ 4\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ Your neck is like the Tower of David\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  An erect stature is beauty in a woman, and the allegorical 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ meaning is that [just as] the Tower of David, which is the Citadel of Zion, is a place of strength, a 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ tower, and a fortress, so is your neck. This is the Chamber of Hewn Stone, which was Israels strength 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ and fortification, and that tower was built as a model, and was built for beauty, so that everyone 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ should look at it to learn its forms and the beauty of its architecture, and the word \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ (לתלפיות)\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  is of the 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ grammatical structure of (Job 35:11): He teaches us \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ (מלפנו)\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  more than the beasts of the earth, and 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ the tav in \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ תלפיות\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  is like the tav in \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ תרמית\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  (guile) and \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ תבנית\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  (form). \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ a thousand shields hanging on it 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ It was the custom of the princes to hang their shields and their quivers on the walls of the towers. 
\lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ quivers\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  Heb. \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ שלטי\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , the quivers in which they place arrows, like (Jer. 51:11): Polish the arrows, fill 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ the quivers \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ (השלטים)\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , and similar to this is the Chamber of Hewn Stone, whence instruction goes 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ forth, for the Torah is a shield to Israel, (rendering \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ אלף המגן\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  as: the teaching that is a shield). It is also 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ possible to render \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ אלף המגן\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  as \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ מגן האלף\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , the shield of the thousand, alluding to (I Chron. 16:15): the 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ word He had commanded to the thousandth [\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ לאלף\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ ] generation. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ all the quivers of the mighty men\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  We 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ find that disciples are symbolized by arrows and quivers, as is stated (Ps. 127:4f.): As arrows in the 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ hand of a mighty man, so are the sons of ones youth. Happy is the man who has filled his quiver with 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ them.  
