\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ are pleasant to me. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ the sun\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  Heb. \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ היום\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , usually the day. This refers to the sun, and likewise, (Gen. 3: 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ 8): in the direction of the sun \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ (לרוח היום)\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ , and so, (Mal. 3:19): For lo, the sun \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ (היום)\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  comes, glowing 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ like a furnace, and when the sun spreads, I will go to Mount Moriah, to the everlasting Temple. [This 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ is] in Genesis Rabbah (55:7). i.e., When they will then sin before Me by profaning My sacred offerings 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ and by spurning My meal offerings in the days of Hophni and Phinehas (I Sam. 3:12-17), I will 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ withdraw from them and I will abandon this Tabernacle, and I will choose for Myself Mount Moriah, 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ the everlasting Temple, and there, You are all fair...and there is no blemish in you, and there I will 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ accept all your sacrifices.  
\par \par }

